{{champion:98}} 

The definition of denial. Nothing like saving someone with a sliver of health, making someone's towerdive go RIP, or turning a 4v4 into a 5v5 whilst your Zz'rots ticks rips apart some poor tower with no retaliation or defence available against it.

{{champion:202}} 

Doing well as Jhin feels good and the champion himself has such atmosphere and feeling to him. When I play him, and succeed on him, it just feels like nothing else. It feels masterful, powerful, and just generally internally rewarding. I'd like to think it's because of how tricky he can be to play compared to the more easy match ups he runs into, though.

{{champion:90}} 

He's just incredibly annoying to deal with and fucks over so many AD champions that often are his targets and until you get QSS he's basically impossible to kill without CC that can somehow apply after his ult. I like to go RoA and Zz'rots and laugh whilst my opponents can do nothing because I'm too tanky and I push like a bulldozer because I exist.

My main is {{champion:90}} .

Because I love making cancer assassins cry. QSS and Maw? lol Malz AD.

